<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Morphological characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Szepligeti" baseAuthorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Neocardiochiles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neocardiochiles fasciipennis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Neocardiochiles fasciipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are only known from holotype. The species is distinguished from other members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szepligeti" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Neocardiochiles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neocardiochiles" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Neocardiochiles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: body ~ 11 mm; posterior margin of mesopleuron smooth; basal spur on hind tibia slightly shorter than the half length of hind basitarsus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neocardiochiles fasciipennis A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D ventro-lateral hypopygium; arrow: median longitudinal fold E dorsal propodeum and T 1 - T 3" figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.84937.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706720" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">6A</figureCitation>
); forewing length ~ 13 mm; T1 ~ 1.35 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than apical width (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Neocardiochiles fasciipennis A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D ventro-lateral hypopygium; arrow: median longitudinal fold E dorsal propodeum and T 1 - T 3" figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.84937.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706720" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">6E</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath as long as hind tarsomeres 1-3 combined.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/jhr.91.84937.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706720" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
